Having taken a new copy of the hl7v2.core in CVS, I get a new location for this same error. The "name" variable is null and this causes a nullPointerException.

Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NullPointerException
 at org.eclipse.ohf.hl7v2.core.definitions.model.DataTypeDefn.escapable(DataTypeDefn.java:47)

changing this:
public boolean escapable() {
     return name.equals("ST") || name.equals("TX") || name.equals("FT") || name.equals("CF") || name.charAt(0) == '*';
}
to:
public boolean escapable() {
	if (name == null) {
		int lastSep = getPath().lastIndexOf(PATH_SEPARATOR);
		name = getPath().substring(lastSep+1);
	}
	return name.equals("ST") || name.equals("TX") || name.equals("FT") || name.equals("CF") || name.charAt(0) == '*';
}

(ie working off the path variable instead of the name variable keeps the program running)

