In my own workaround for this bug, I have over-ridden getHelpContextIds as shown below, to return a help context id specific to the object shown in the property sheet.  This means that context-sensitive help can be implemented appropriately for each different object if desired, rather than simply for the Properties view.

	/**
	 * Over-ridden to correct bug 151056.
	 * <p>
	 * The contextId returned will generally be of the form
	 * "com.rolemodellers.rim.<model element interface>", e.g.,
	 * "com.rolemodellers.rim.Identity".
	 * 
	 * @see org.eclipse.emf.edit.provider.ItemPropertyDescriptor#getHelpContextIds(java.lang.Object)
	 */
	@Override
	public Object getHelpContextIds(Object object) {
		String contextId = null;
		try {
			contextId = ((EStructuralFeature) getFeature(this))
					.getContainerClass().getName();
		} catch (Exception e) {
			contextId = "org.eclipse.ui.property_sheet_page_help_context";
		}
		return contextId;
	}

